00:32:46.967 --> 00:32:48.237
You didn't know, did you?

00:32:48.237 --> 00:32:50.170
I'm staying next door.

00:32:54.276 --> 00:32:56.609
Just a second.

00:33:01.798 --> 00:33:04.073
Here it is.

00:33:04.073 --> 00:33:05.919
Thank you so much.

00:33:08.789 --> 00:33:10.772
The wind in Jeju

00:33:10.772 --> 00:33:13.092
is no joke.

00:33:14.161 --> 00:33:16.261
Yeah, the pants are fixed.

00:33:16.261 --> 00:33:20.166
Luckily, someone at the lobby had a sewing kit.

00:33:21.034 --> 00:33:22.721
You must be very handy.

00:33:22.721 --> 00:33:24.111
Not really.

00:33:24.111 --> 00:33:26.041
I just made sure

00:33:26.041 --> 00:33:28.208
it looks decent, so it doesn't show.

00:33:32.546 --> 00:33:35.148
What are you doing for dinner?

00:33:36.828 --> 00:33:38.482
I'm just going to grab
something quick in my room.

00:33:38.482 --> 00:33:41.515
Don't rush a meal. Every meal matters.

00:33:41.515 --> 00:33:44.076
Try the Italian place in the Ocean Wing.

00:33:44.076 --> 00:33:46.059
It's pretty solid.

00:33:48.629 --> 00:33:51.755
Want to grab dinner together?

00:33:51.755 --> 00:33:55.201
I'm alone during free time too.

00:34:29.171 --> 00:34:31.404
I guess I'm just not great at this.

00:35:02.465 --> 00:35:03.973
I saw you booked

00:35:03.973 --> 00:35:07.040
the yacht tour for tomorrow.

00:35:08.444 --> 00:35:10.045
Yes.

00:35:14.481 --> 00:35:17.583
I signed up because my wife would've loved it.

00:35:19.305 --> 00:35:20.953
But recently,

00:35:22.622 --> 00:35:24.991
she passed away.

00:35:25.739 --> 00:35:27.335
Oh...

00:35:28.330 --> 00:35:30.596
I wished we could've come together,

00:35:31.105 --> 00:35:33.166
but it's too late now.

00:35:35.945 --> 00:35:37.804
You still came.

00:35:41.511 --> 00:35:43.643
That matters.

00:35:48.915 --> 00:35:51.085
- Happy birthday to you.
- Happy birthday to you.

00:35:51.085 --> 00:35:53.186
- Happy birthday to you.
- Happy birthday to you.

00:35:53.186 --> 00:35:57.990
- Happy birthday to my dear Sol.
- Happy birthday to my dear Sol.

00:36:02.939 --> 00:36:06.232
No, please. Don't do that.

00:36:23.205 --> 00:36:25.017
Just a moment.

00:36:27.405 --> 00:36:29.288
Just a moment.

00:36:42.905 --> 00:36:43.938
What are you doing?

00:36:43.938 --> 00:36:46.640
Please go outside.

00:36:46.640 --> 00:36:48.274
It's okay. Let's step out.

00:36:50.039 --> 00:36:51.911
They won't allow it.

00:36:52.939 --> 00:36:54.606
You can't smoke in here.

00:36:54.606 --> 00:36:56.382
You have to go outside.

00:37:01.105 --> 00:37:03.973
What's going on?

00:37:03.973 --> 00:37:05.691
Just let it all out.

00:37:27.320 --> 00:37:29.172
Thank you

00:37:29.172 --> 00:37:31.384
so much for today.

00:37:35.731 --> 00:37:37.329
Well...

00:37:39.006 --> 00:37:41.894
you didn't come here
with bad intentions, right?

00:37:42.398 --> 00:37:44.166
Sorry?

00:37:44.166 --> 00:37:46.199
That would be very troubling.

00:37:49.603 --> 00:37:52.572
I'm a person of faith.

00:37:53.409 --> 00:37:54.539
Then

00:37:54.539 --> 00:37:56.609
I suppose there's nothing to worry about.

00:37:59.112 --> 00:38:01.858
But has anything like that happened here?

00:38:01.858 --> 00:38:02.749
Pardon?

00:38:02.749 --> 00:38:04.707
I mean people who come here to end it all.

00:38:05.619 --> 00:38:07.656
Yes, there was a case quite a while back.

00:38:07.656 --> 00:38:09.956
On the Camino de Santiago.

00:38:11.358 --> 00:38:13.358
I really enjoyed today.

00:38:13.358 --> 00:38:15.561
Same here.

00:38:38.347 --> 00:38:40.286
Call me when you wrap up.

00:38:51.505 --> 00:38:52.872
It's me.

00:38:52.872 --> 00:38:54.935
I'm all done now.

00:38:54.935 --> 00:38:56.569
That took ages.

00:38:56.569 --> 00:38:58.805
That kid really owes his mom everything.

00:38:58.805 --> 00:39:01.706
Labor was brutal.

00:39:01.706 --> 00:39:05.006
I'm wiped out and starving too.

00:39:05.006 --> 00:39:05.979
Get here soon.

00:39:05.979 --> 00:39:08.272
I didn't eat,

00:39:08.272 --> 00:39:09.741
waiting to eat with you.

00:39:09.741 --> 00:39:11.520
Still?

00:39:11.520 --> 00:39:13.619
You should've gone ahead.

00:39:15.080 --> 00:39:17.857
Oh right. There's nothing to eat at home.

00:39:18.460 --> 00:39:21.697
How about those noodles
we missed out on earlier?

00:39:21.697 --> 00:39:22.965
Sounds good.

00:39:22.965 --> 00:39:24.380
Hurry over.

00:39:24.380 --> 00:39:25.967
Okay.

00:39:31.871 --> 00:39:33.906
[The Man Next Door]

00:39:40.013 --> 00:39:43.716
[Do Hyun]

00:40:24.811 --> 00:40:28.361
Darn it... I'm beyond saving.

00:40:53.073 --> 00:40:54.754
Thank you.

00:40:59.893 --> 00:41:02.395
Go ahead. I'll be fine.

00:41:13.339 --> 00:41:16.712
[Please let this work]

00:41:16.712 --> 00:41:19.612
Being alone is survivable.

00:41:20.947 --> 00:41:23.272
But even then,

00:41:23.272 --> 00:41:26.272
you still need someone who'll tell you

00:41:26.272 --> 00:41:28.754
it's okay to be alone.

00:41:30.893 --> 00:41:34.006
Honore de Balzac.

00:41:34.006 --> 00:41:34.928
Sorry about that.

00:41:34.928 --> 00:41:37.897
How's your night going?

00:41:37.897 --> 00:41:40.772
If you're feeling lonely right now,

00:41:40.772 --> 00:41:41.968
I can say it for you.

00:41:41.968 --> 00:41:43.672
That'll be 9,000 won.

00:41:43.672 --> 00:41:47.606
That being alone is still okay.

00:41:55.105 --> 00:41:56.882
You're back?

00:42:00.055 --> 00:42:01.854
Hungry, right?

00:42:09.138 --> 00:42:12.072
I called maintenance for the washer.

00:42:12.072 --> 00:42:13.966
Turns out it was broken.

00:42:16.047 --> 00:42:18.237
It was new.

00:42:19.038 --> 00:42:22.041
My place, usually pitch-black,

00:42:24.739 --> 00:42:26.980
finally felt

00:42:26.980 --> 00:42:29.551
like it was glad

00:42:29.551 --> 00:42:31.350
What are you doing?

00:42:32.498 --> 00:42:35.855
- to see me.
- Nice! Good call.

00:42:37.157 --> 00:42:39.291
Go wash up.

00:42:56.645 --> 00:42:58.011
How is it?

00:42:58.011 --> 00:42:59.712
It's delicious.

00:43:02.251 --> 00:43:04.281
Only "delicious"?

00:43:05.054 --> 00:43:07.045
Nothing else with it?

00:43:07.045 --> 00:43:08.888
Like what?

00:43:10.290 --> 00:43:12.258
Well...

00:43:12.258 --> 00:43:14.059
Nothing that hits the heart?

00:43:15.564 --> 00:43:17.530
Are you asking for praise?

00:43:21.601 --> 00:43:23.836
Most dishes, sure,

00:43:24.404 --> 00:43:25.806
but curry's different.

00:43:25.806 --> 00:43:27.876
It should be mostly comfortable.

00:43:27.876 --> 00:43:29.475
Why's that?

00:43:31.211 --> 00:43:33.479
Curry's my comfort food.

00:43:34.237 --> 00:43:37.505
Back when I was broke,
freezing, and scraping by as a musician,

00:43:37.505 --> 00:43:40.352
I'd grab a 1,000-won curry powder packet,

00:43:41.223 --> 00:43:43.073
throw in just potatoes

00:43:43.073 --> 00:43:47.427
and onions, make a big batch,

00:43:47.427 --> 00:43:48.672
and day two,

00:43:48.672 --> 00:43:50.006
day three,

00:43:50.006 --> 00:43:51.772
it tasted deeper,

00:43:51.772 --> 00:43:54.667
and somehow even better.

00:43:58.238 --> 00:44:00.172
Like it levels up overnight.

00:44:02.542 --> 00:44:04.978
I formed this tiny fantasy.

00:44:04.978 --> 00:44:06.246
What kind?

00:44:06.246 --> 00:44:07.880
One night,

00:44:09.105 --> 00:44:10.916
I come home wiped out

00:44:11.472 --> 00:44:14.353
for no good reason,

00:44:16.222 --> 00:44:18.724
and there she is, apron on,

00:44:19.872 --> 00:44:21.760
stirring curry,

00:44:22.595 --> 00:44:24.105
that smell taking over

00:44:24.105 --> 00:44:26.832
the entire apartment.

00:44:31.315 --> 00:44:33.106
Well...

00:44:33.106 --> 00:44:35.007
That's a pretty simple wish.

00:44:35.708 --> 00:44:37.910
But there's a catch.

00:44:39.379 --> 00:44:41.172
The wife

00:44:41.172 --> 00:44:44.350
has to have the apron on and nothing else.

00:44:46.085 --> 00:44:47.816
- Ugh, you perv.
- You'll actually do it, right?

00:44:47.816 --> 00:44:49.758
- Me?
- Yeah.

00:44:49.758 --> 00:44:52.124
You're out of your mind.

00:44:53.159 --> 00:44:55.639
Please make my wish come true.

00:44:55.639 --> 00:44:57.096
That's ridiculous.

00:45:06.539 --> 00:45:09.642
I've never seen you laugh this easily.

00:45:12.478 --> 00:45:14.614
You tagged along so I wouldn't hole up

00:45:14.614 --> 00:45:16.282
in my room acting all tough, right?

00:45:16.282 --> 00:45:18.418
Man, guiding must be such a grind.

00:45:18.418 --> 00:45:20.486
Not at all.

00:45:20.486 --> 00:45:22.255
I get to travel for free, as much as I want,

00:45:22.255 --> 00:45:24.791
and they pay me too. It's honestly the best.

00:45:24.791 --> 00:45:27.660
And the yacht ride is the most expensive add-on
in the whole package.

00:45:27.660 --> 00:45:29.528
Oh, really?

00:45:38.538 --> 00:45:41.273
Being somewhere this nice
makes me think of my husband.

00:45:41.990 --> 00:45:45.531
We never got around to a yacht trip together.

00:45:45.531 --> 00:45:47.130
You still can.

00:45:47.130 --> 00:45:49.581
There will be another chance.

00:45:50.616 --> 00:45:53.919
I lost mine too. Ten years ago.

00:46:08.201 --> 00:46:10.239
This tastes nothing like

00:46:10.239 --> 00:46:12.274
what I used to eat in Seoul.

00:46:12.274 --> 00:46:14.104
Try the turban shell too.

00:46:14.104 --> 00:46:17.305
The haenyeo ladies pulled it
from the water right here.

00:46:33.095 --> 00:46:35.194
"Too salty."

00:46:35.931 --> 00:46:37.896
"Too spicy."

00:46:39.201 --> 00:46:41.800
My wife used to get on me
about that all the time.

00:46:43.774 --> 00:46:46.839
And now the one who only ate clean
isn't here anymore.

00:46:48.034 --> 00:46:50.242
Funny how that works.

00:47:06.814 --> 00:47:08.764
Hey, look over there.

00:47:08.764 --> 00:47:11.722
See that group?

00:47:11.722 --> 00:47:13.002
Yeah.

00:47:13.002 --> 00:47:15.000
Keep this quiet, okay?

00:47:15.638 --> 00:47:19.155
Their deal is a little different.

00:47:19.155 --> 00:47:21.006
Different how?

00:47:22.115 --> 00:47:24.555
It's the "Erase-It" package.

00:47:24.555 --> 00:47:26.478
- Erase it?
- Shh.

00:47:29.816 --> 00:47:32.988
They look cheerful,

00:47:32.988 --> 00:47:37.322
but they're going through it.

00:47:39.992 --> 00:47:42.028
They picked this

00:47:42.028 --> 00:47:44.831
just to block it out for a bit.

00:47:44.831 --> 00:47:46.566
When they head home,

00:47:46.566 --> 00:47:50.169
real life's still waiting, exactly the same.

